Are you looking to make your next career move? CellCarta, a Contract Research Organization, is hiring a Director, Global Infrastructure \\& Architecture (Hybrid) to join our dynamic team. As a Director, Global Infrastructure \\& Architecture (Hybrid), you will have the opportunity to use your expertise and skills to ensure that our services meet the highest industry standards. Come work with a team of talented individuals who are committed to making a positive impact on human health and well\\-being. Apply today and take the first step towards an exciting new career with CellCarta!




**Summary**
 As part of the Global IT leadership, CellCarta is looking for a Director, Global Infrastructure \\& Architecture (Hybrid). You will focus on a variety of new and changing technology designs for CellCarta’s businesses. This role requires hands\\-on experience in networking, infrastructure \\& server setup (both on\\-premise and cloud), as well as in managing technical people. With the implementation of a hybrid cloud strategy, you will have the ability to work with the newest tools and environments and advise on our implementation and future needs.




**Responsibilities**
 More specifically, you will participate in the following:




* Lead a technical architect team (currently 2 people);
* Partner with CellCarta’s businesses and global functions to understand their needs and provide appropriate technology solutions;
* Advise on best\\-fit (IT) solutions to support Business and IT strategy;
* Design infrastructure and networking at a global scale;
* Design secure implementations and integrations of end\\-user devices and lab equipment;
* Design network solutions together with cloud providers and internet providers, keeping in mind security and segregation;
* Work closely with operations and support staff, as well as external vendors, to implement cloud, data center, and network solutions;
* Support labs in implementing new devices or configuring them in the networks/on platforms;
* Support both local (small) virtual server environments as well as AWS/Azure environments – including server, storage, and network setup;
* Implement configurations / modifications in technical applications to ensure compliance with solution designs and company standards;
* Serve as a “final tier” technical subject matter expert (SME) for support issues which are not able to be resolved by operations staff;
* Support Annual Operating Plan development and project budget estimation;
* Influence annual IT roadmap (application \\& business);
* Develop and maintain a technical standards catalog for the enterprise


**Education**
* An advanced degree (Bachelor’s level or higher in science or IT)


**Main Requirements**
* \\>5 years of experience in similar roles with a proven track record of delivering (technical \\& strategical) designs in a global environment;
* An IT consultancy background or experience with a variety of IT environments and applications;
* Proven experience with multiple technologies including on\\-premises and cloud environments (such as AWS, Azure, or GCP);
* Proven experience in developing complex solution architectures, including application and data flow optimization;
* Proven experience in working with internal teams and external vendors in different sourcing models;
* Proven experience in designing robust solutions to meet requirements for high availability, disaster recovery, and information security;
* Understanding of contemporary project management models such as agile and waterfall;
* Experience in setting up end\\-user devices and hybrid server environments including storage and network configurations;
* Experience in configuring Windows servers (required); Linux administration skills (preferred);
* An understanding of typical laboratory workflows in the biopharmaceutical, environmental, or similar industries (preferred);
* Knowledge of or experience with GxP processes (preferred);
* A wide degree of creativity and initiative. This includes helping the team operationally where needed by demonstrating engagement, energy, and enthusiasm;
* Strong communication skills, both verbal and written;
* Fluency in English both written and spoken. Additional languages such as Dutch and French preferred;
* Strong organizational skills, a results oriented mindset, proven teamwork characteristics, and ability to work independently


**Working Conditions**
* Preferred locations are Montreal, Canada; Antwerp, Belgium; or Naperville, United States;
* Hybrid work arrangement


**Benefits**
**We offer a wide range of benefits including:**
* Competitive Wages ($120,000 \\- $150,000 USD);
* Medical, Dental, and Vision Benefits;
* 401k Retirement Savings Plan with a Healthy Match;
* Employee Annual Incentive Plan (EAIP);
* Employee Assistance Program (EAP);
* Vacation and Sick Time;
* Referral Program;
* Career Advancement Opportunities


**About CellCarta**
 CellCartais a leading provider of specialized precision medicine laboratory services to the biopharmaceutical industry. Leveraging its integrated analytical platforms in immunology, histopathology, proteomics, and genomics, as well as related specimen collection and logistics services, CellCarta supports the entire drug development cycle, from discovery to late\\-stage clinical trials. The Company operates globally with facilities located in Canada, USA, Belgium, Australia, and China.




 Joining CellCarta means working with dedicated professionals who are focused on achieving our mission of impacting the future of patient therapy. We make a difference in the lives of patients around the world!




**Join us as we make an impact on patient therapy!**
 The information collected to review your application will be processed by the human resources services of CellCarta Biosciences Inc. and its affiliates (collectively, “CellCarta”). The legal basis for this processing is the legitimate interest of CellCarta to evaluate the suitability of candidates for the roles available at CellCarta.




 CellCarta will only process that information which is necessary to evaluate your application. This information includes identifying information such as your name, address, email address and phone number, as well as information about your education and professional experience, including previous positions and your CV. Such information is required for us to complete your applicant file, assess your suitability for the role and comply with applicable laws. CellCarta may obtain personal information from other sources, such as during reference, background, or employment checks, with your permission, and from third party sources such as recruitment and assessment sites or professional social media sites, in each case only if such information is relevant to reviewing your application. Your personal information will be retained only for so long as reasonably necessary and in accordance with applicable laws. This information will be processed confidentially and only accessed by those who have a need for the recruitment process. Please note that the information comprising your applicant file may be processed in a country that is not where you are located (for example, you might be in the European Economic Area or Québec, Canada, whereas your applicant file may be reviewed by CellCarta in the United States). If you are offered and accept employment with CellCarta Biosciences Inc. or one of its affiliates, the information collected will become part of your employment record. If you do not want us to retain your information, or want us to update it, please contact privacy@cellcarta.com.




